Former President Goodluck Jonathan on Saturday visited his security aide, Inspector Gambo Joseph, who was injured in the Wednesday’s auto crash within the vicinity of the Nnamdi Azikiwe Airport, Abuja. Jonathan expressed joy that the injured officer was responding to treatment and recovering fast.   Bandits abduct wife, daughter of Plateau commissioner     I’ve forgiven those who attacked, burnt my palace,…     Amaechi and implications of Electoral Act’s Section 84 (12)   He also stated that the second officer, Inspector Michael Ebute, who sustained injury during the accident, was discharged on Friday. “Thank God Gambo is recovering so fast. I am pleased to inform you that the second officer, Michael, has been discharged and returned to his family,” he said. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that two police officers were reported dead during the accident which involved a car conveying them from the airport.